The paper proposes a new algorithm for learning latent-variable probabilistic graphical models, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG). The algorithm uses techniques such as predictive state representation and reproducing-kernel Hilbert space embeddings, which are also commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and signal processing (cs.SI). The experiments involve tasks related to computer vision (cs.CV) and computational biology, which could also fall under the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT) due to the probabilistic nature of the models.
